        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "chore: rename ClawHub admin package",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Rename the private operator package from `packages/clawhub-mod` / `@openclaw/clawhub-mod` to `packages/clawhub-admin` / `@openclaw/clawhub-admin`.\n- Rename the binary and command surface to `clawhub-admin`, update repo scripts/config/docs/specs, and remove the old top-level compatibility aliases (`ban-user`, `unban-user`, `set-role`).\n- Add a package-layout regression test covering the new package identity and removed legacy command aliases.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `mkdir -p packages/clawhub-mod/dist && bunx vitest run scripts/package-layout.test.ts; exit_code=$?; rm -rf packages/clawhub-mod; exit $exit_code`\n- `bunx vitest run scripts/package-layout.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bunx vitest run -c vitest.e2e.config.ts e2e/clawhub.e2e.test.ts --testNamePattern \"does not expose removed admin compatibility aliases\"` (exited 0; skipped because the token-gated role-help suite is not enabled in this environment)\n",
